festival.introText: Neighbourhood Weekender will be returning to Warrington, bringing you another incredible weekend of live music featuring some of the biggest bands and hottest new artists over 3 stages.
festival.descriptionText: Get more information about Neighbourhood Weekender 2023 including festival tickets, news, reviews and lineups.

reviews.title: Review of Neighbourhood Weekender 2021
reviews.body: The lack of trains available really spoiled the headliners as we had to leave early to ensure we could get home. There were also some questionable guests who spoiled the atmosphere slightly.

faqs.question: Does Neighbourhood Weekender have onsite camping?
faqs.answer: No, Neighbourhood Weekender is a non camping festival so camping equipment is not needed however there is plenty of alternative accommodation to choose from.

faqs.question: When is Neighbourhood Weekender 2023?
faqs.answer: Neighbourhood Weekender returns to Victoria Park on Saturday 27th - Sunday 28th May 2023.

faqs.question: How do I get to Neighbourhood Weekender?
faqs.answer:
By Car - The designated car park is situated 10 minutes from the festival site. 

By Coach - Big Green Coach is the official travel partner for Neighbourhood Weekender, running services from Chester, Crewe, Leeds, Liverpool, Bradford, Huddersfield, Stockport, Stoke-on-Trent, Sheffield, Birkenhead, Lancaster, Wigan, Preston and Manchester.

 

By Rail - Warrington Bank Quay and Warrington Central are the two train stations in Warrington, both just a 20 minute walk from Victoria Park

How much are Neighbourhood Weekender tickets?

Head to the tickets section above for the latest prices.

faqs.question: Where is Neighbourhood Weekender?
faqs.answer: Neighbourhood Weekender is located in Victoria Park, Warrington. The postcode is WA4 1DG.

faqs.question: What happens If I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer:
Unfortunately we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent.

 

Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

faqs.question: Does Neighbourhood Weekender have any age restrictions?
How do I access my tickets?
faqs.answer: Dependant on your delivery method (RapidScan or Posted) you can view your order at any time by logging into ww.skiddle.com/orders or the 'my tickets' section of the Skiddle app. From here you will be able to view the status of your delivery or access your RapidScan barcoded tickets.

faqs.question: Can I bring my own food and drink into Neighbourhood Weekender?
faqs.answer: You are not allowed to bring your own food and drink into Neighbourhood Weekender. There will be a wide variety of food and drink stalls inside the festival, serving up organic, vegetarian and vegan options.

faqs.question: What are the set times?
faqs.answer: The set times are generally released on the first day of the festival.
